stateless functional component:
JS fn, returns html element

function Welcome (props) {
    return <h1> Hello {props.name} </h1>;
}


stateful class component:
Class extending Component class, must render() and return an html element

class Welcome extends React.Component{
    render(){
	return <h1> Hello {this.props.name} </h1>
    }
}


functional components:
.simple functions
.use functional component as much as possible
.absence of 'this'

class components:
.feature rich
.maintain privte date (state)
.complex UI logic
.provide lifecycle hooks
.called as smart/cotainer components
	
